 <p>DDCcontrol is a program running on Linux, used to control monitor
 parameters, like brightness and contrast, by software, i.e. without using the
 OSD (On Screen Display) and the buttons in front of the monitor.</p>
 <p>For more informations see <a href="doc/index.html" class="olink"> the
 documentation</a>.</p>
